<p>October 1915</p>
<p>Friday 29</p>
<p>Tent pitching &amp; odd jobs.</p>
<p>Turkish fire very heavy in morning</p>
<p>Several shells fell in over our camp &amp; a great number just over the hill.</p>
<p>Shrapnel falling all over the place.</p>
<p>Roberts hit by spent pellet, but only bruised.</p>
<p>Jack [indecipherable] &amp; two others sent away on the sick list.</p>
<p>The number of sick sent away is alarming.</p>
<p>Heard that Allied troops are landing at Salonica to help Servians.</p>
